## Early game

The Void has a noticeably better Control Module drop chance than any main
planet, and **Hepit** (Capture, levels 10-15) is a short, low-level way to
farm it: Control Modules come from mission-completion rewards rather than
regular enemy kills, so a couple of quick runs back-to-back beats a long
mission. **Teshub** (Exterminate) on the same tileset is a good alternative if
Hepit's matchmaking is slow.

## Mid & late game

The wiki doesn't call out a distinct late-game Control Module node beyond
"the Void has better odds," so the natural extension for a Steel Path squad is
an endless Void Survival like **Mot** — it gives the longest uninterrupted
window to rack up completion rewards and rotation drops in one sitting. Since
Control Modules are reward-based rather than an enemy drop, neither Resource
Drop Boosters nor the Steel Path passive increase them; run length is what
matters.

